{#-
  ScrollArea — Custom-styled scrollable container.

  Pure CSS. 0 Stimulus controller. The browser owns scroll behavior — we
  only style the scrollbar. Preserves native momentum scroll on iOS / Android
  (the kit's custom scrollbar styling via `::-webkit-scrollbar` +
  `scrollbar-width: thin` + `scrollbar-color` is compatible with
  `-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch`).

  Direction-aware: the browser flips scrollbar position natively in RTL via
  `<html dir="rtl">` — no kit code needed. Logical CSS (`overflow-inline`,
  `overflow-block`) provides the axis abstraction.

  Per OQ-34 doctrine "natif d'abord" sealed S2.4 opening — no library
  adapter (OverlayScrollbars / SimpleBar deferred to a future amend ADR if
  cross-browser scrollbar styling drift surfaces).

  Composes (no explicit deps): used as a wrap around any tall/wide content.
  DataTable (S2.4b) will compose ScrollArea around its `<table>` when the
  consumer's data exceeds the viewport's inline-size.

  Parameters:
    htmlId          (string,  optional) — auto-generated.
    orientation     (string,  optional) — both (default) | vertical | horizontal.
                                          Controls which axes can scroll.
    size            (string,  optional) — sm (thin scrollbar 6 px) | md (default,
                                          10 px) | lg (14 px). The visible
                                          scrollbar width.
    maxBlockSize    (string,  optional) — CSS value clamping the block-axis
                                          (e.g. '320px', '60vh'). Required for
                                          vertical scrolling to engage when
                                          content overflows.
    maxInlineSize   (string,  optional) — CSS value clamping the inline-axis.
                                          Required for horizontal scrolling.
    className       (string,  optional) — extra classes on the wrap.

  Blocks:
    body (required) — the scrollable content.

  Usage:

    {% embed '@cremona/components/scroll-area/scroll-area.html.twig' with {
      orientation: 'vertical',
      maxBlockSize: '320px',
      size: 'md',
    } %}
      {% block body %}
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. …</p>
        … plenty of vertically-overflowing content …
      {% endblock %}
    {% endembed %}
-#}

{%- set htmlId        = htmlId        | default('cremona-scroll-area-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set orientation   = orientation   | default('both') -%}
{%- set size          = size          | default('md') -%}
{%- set maxBlockSize  = maxBlockSize  | default(null) -%}
{%- set maxInlineSize = maxInlineSize | default(null) -%}
{%- set className     = className     | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-scroll-area'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set _style = '' -%}
{%- if maxBlockSize -%}{%- set _style = _style ~ 'max-block-size:' ~ maxBlockSize ~ ';' -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if maxInlineSize -%}{%- set _style = _style ~ 'max-inline-size:' ~ maxInlineSize ~ ';' -%}{%- endif -%}

<div
  id="{{ htmlId }}"
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-orientation="{{ orientation }}"
  data-size="{{ size }}"
  {%- if _style %} style="{{ _style }}"{% endif -%}
>
  {%- block body -%}{%- endblock -%}
</div>
